        "content": "Ceiling fan blade span (diameter) should match room size for optimal air circulation coverage. Industry standards and our installation experience recommend the following blade spans based on room square footage: Up to 75 sq ft (small bathrooms, closets, laundry rooms): 29-36 inch blade span fans—These compact fans fit tight spaces while providing adequate air circulation for small rooms. Example rooms: 6x10 bathroom, 8x9 laundry room, walk-in closet. 76-144 sq ft (bedrooms, home offices, breakfast nooks): 36-42 inch blade span fans—Mid-size fans suitable for most bedrooms and standard rooms. Example rooms: 10x12 bedroom, 11x13 guest room, 9x14 office. 145-225 sq ft (master bedrooms, dining rooms, family rooms): 44-50 inch blade span fans—Large fans providing strong air circulation for bigger living spaces. Example rooms: 12x15 master bedroom, 13x17 family room, 14x16 dining room. 226-400 sq ft (great rooms, large living areas, combined spaces): 52-56 inch blade span fans—Extra-large fans for spacious rooms requiring substantial airflow. Example rooms: 15x18 great room, 16x20 living room, 18x22 combined living/dining. 400+ sq ft (two-story great rooms, commercial spaces, large outdoor patios): 60-72 inch blade span fans OR multiple fans—Oversized fans or multiple fan strategy for maximum coverage. For rooms exceeding 400 sq ft, installing two properly-sized fans often provides better air circulation than one extremely large fan, eliminating dead zones and creating more even air distribution throughout the space."
